.TH LPF-SYSCTL 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.2.1" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-sysctl \- check or diff kernel sysctl parameters
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf sysctl <check|diff|apply>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Check, diff, or apply kernel sysctl parameters required by lpf.
check mode reads required sysctls from /proc/sys and prints key=value pairs.
diff mode snapshots observed sysctls and diffs them against the required set.
apply mode writes required sysctls that are not already set to 1.
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf sysctl check
lpf sysctl diff
lpf sysctl apply
.SH FILES
/proc/sys
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-apply(8), sysctl(8)
